<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/238–C.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gummeré</persName>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d617fn1">Mutatis mutandis to Paris, No. 278; London, No.
                                230; Rome, No. 204; Vienna No 259; Brussels, No. 176; The Hague, No.
                                13: Stockholm, No. 108; Lisbon, No. 170; St. Petersburg, No.
                                188.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-22"><hi rend="italic">October 22,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 162.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I quote a telegram sent to you by the
                            department on the 20th instant.<note n="2" xml:id="d617fn2">Supra.</note></p>
                        <p>I inclose for your information a copy of the draft submitted by the
                            French ambassador and Spanish chargé, as well as a copy of this
                            department’s memorandum in response.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>